news.title: Lucknow: LDA offers up to Rs 2 lakh discount on flats till June 30
news.para: As per the new discount structure, flats priced up to Rs 45 lakh will receive a concession of Rs 1.5 lakh while those above Rs 45 lakh will be eligible for a Rs 2 lakh discount.

news.title: Three houses built on land earmarked for park demolished in Gurugram’s South City 1
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia, who supervised the operation, said, "The green area is meant to be used as a common area.

news.title: Noida: YEIDA offers 276 residential plots
news.para: Of the total, 214 plots fall under the general category, with 17.5% reserved for farmers and 5% for individuals associated with industries.

news.title: Maharashtra govt will look into stuck housing projects in Pimpri Chinchwad: Deputy CM
news.para: Several projects in PCMC limits and nearby areas have been on hold pending environmental clearances after the Supreme Court in Feb issued a stay on a notification by the Environment Ministry.

news.title: Landowners seek GST relief on joint development agreements
news.para: At the heart of the dispute lies the taxation of development rights transferred by landowners to developers in exchange for a portion of the constructed area or revenue sharing.

news.title: Residents of BPTP in Gurugram oppose revised building plans
news.para: "Over 230 owners have already filed formal objections to the extension of the licence and the in-principle approval of revised plans.

news.title: Amazon leases 3.3 lakh sq ft office space in New York's Bryant Park
news.para: According to a report by The Real Deal, the deal closed last week following initial lease negotiations first revealed by Realty Check in October 2024.

news.title: Banks approach RBI after being directed to raise risk weights to 150%
news.para: Risk weights determine the capital that banks have to set aside to cover credit risk; a higher risk weight leads to more capital requirement for a loan.

news.title: Anant Raj's net profit up 41.40% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Anant Raj's net consolidated total income stood at ₹550.90 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 21.58 per cent from ₹453.12 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Private equity investments dominate as real estate deal volumes surge 133% in Q1 2025: Report
news.para: The surge was driven primarily by private equity (PE) investments, which accounted for 88 per cent of the total deal value, reaffirming institutional interest in income-generating and operationally resilient assets.

news.title: Vijayawada residents seeks to upgrade VMC into GVMC
news.para: Vijayawada municipality was created on April 1, 1888, and was upgraded to a selection-grade municipality in 1960. It was subsequently elevated to a municipal corporation two decades later, in 1981.

news.title: REITs and private equity firms fuel $1 billion in real estate deals in Q1 2025: Report
news.para: Leading the quarter was Mindspace Business Parks REIT’s $234 million acquisition of Sustain Properties, involving 1.82 million sq ft of Grade A office space in Hyderabad's Commerzone Raidurg.

news.title: Brigade Group to jointly develop plots in East Bengaluru
news.para: Spanning approximately 20 acres, the project has a gross development value (GDV) of approximately ₹175 crore and a total development potential of 0.45 million sq ft.

news.title: Illegal constructions demolished along Patiala Ki Rao in Nayagaon, Mohali
news.para: Acting on reports of illegal occupation of approximately 195 feet of the river's width, the team, equipped with two JCB machines, demolished multiple structures that had come up on the riverbed.

news.title: Incuspaze rents 2.5 lakh sq ft office space in Chennai
news.para: Gurugram-based Incuspaze has taken on lease 2.5 lakh square feet of office space at standalone campus 'Olympia Crest', which is located in the heart of Chennai's IT corridor at OMR Zone 1.

news.title: TREVOC Group plans to invest ₹200 crore to expand in Haryana
news.para: The company will construct 3–5 projects across 10–25 acre land parcels each, featuring plotted developments, low-rise gated communities, and hospitality-branded villa projects.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement plans to invest upto ₹3,000 crore to add 4.6 million tonne by FY28
news.para: Arun Shukla, president and director of JK Lakshmi Cement also talked about his plans to scale adjacent businesses like AAC Blocks and RMC, aiming to double their revenue contribution to ₹1,000 crore within a year.

news.title: Chandigarh residents associations seeks MP intervention on civic issues
news.para: Crawfed installed a symbolic board listing major public issues lingering for many years, and the MP and former mayor were asked to sign, which they refused.

news.title: Nagpur police registers six cases on illegal sand mining in Ramtek
news.para: The next day, four more tippers involved in illegal sand transportation were intercepted. At Chargaon Road, driver Kamlesh Athawale was caught with 12 brass sand and a vehicle worth Rs40 lakh.

news.title: AIF infuse ₹73,903 crore in Indian real estate till 9M FY25: Anarock
news.para: By the end of 9M FY25, AIF investments in real estate rose from ₹68,540 crore by FY 2024-end to ₹73,903 crore - an eight per cent growth in first three quarters of fiscal year 2025.
